						<p>In the context of the article, "right" is understood as a grant from an authority. Using a right necessarily reinforces both said authority and the submissive relationship with it. Oposite to this, freedom. So if there's a spring, freely taking water means one thing, rightfully taking water means quite another.</p>
						</li>

